OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1775927152
OL,3,CNI political leader write to Starmer
OL,4,Crequesting action against fuel costs
OL,6,FThe Ulster Unionist Party has said any
OL,7,Fdemonstrations must remain lawful.
OL,9,FA party spokesperson said: "The Ulster
OL,10,FUnionist Party fully understands the
OL,11,Ffrustrations being felt by everyone
OL,12,Fand businesses across Northern Ireland
OL,13,Fwho are being hammered by sky-high
OL,14,Ffuel costs.
OL,16,F"We also recognise the serious
OL,17,Fpressures facing our farmers, who are
OL,18,Fdealing with mounting fertiliser costs
OL,19,Fthat will inevitably have knock-on
OL,20,Feffects on food prices for everyone.
OL,26,@qD@\OUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,447,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1775927152
OL,3,CNI political leader write to Starmer
OL,4,Crequesting action against fuel costs
OL,6,F"Everyone has a legitimate right to
OL,7,Fprotest, but it is a qualified right.
OL,9,F"Any protest must be lawful, must
OL,10,Frespect other people's right to use
OL,11,Fthe road network, to go about their
OL,12,Fdaily lives and to run their
OL,13,Flivelihoods.
OL,15,F"Most importantly, protests must not
OL,16,Fimpede the vital work of our emergency
OL,17,Fservices."
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@AOUwD@AOUyD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/14
